---
description: Use ASCII hyphen (-) instead of em/en dashes in all copy and UI text
alwaysApply: true
---

# Punctuation: hyphens only

Never use em dashes (`—`) or en dashes (`–`) in code, copy, UI strings, messages, comments, or docs for this project.

Always use a plain hyphen-minus (`-`) instead.

Examples:
- Prefer: `India - Available Worldwide`
- Avoid: `India — Available Worldwide`
- Prefer: `Remote-ready - flexible hours`
- Avoid: `Remote-ready — flexible hours`
